<i>♪ Sink back into the ocean ♪</i>

50
00:02:37.724 --> 00:02:39.590
The early reviews
are really good.

51
00:02:41.128 --> 00:02:44.223
So I hear. I. uh. I try not to
pay attention to those things.

52
00:02:45.332 --> 00:02:47.665
I have to admit. I wasn't
such a fan of <i>Descent.</i>

53
00:02:47.734 --> 00:02:51.296
although. clearly. the book
didn't suffer from lack of fans. but...

54
00:02:52.139 --> 00:02:55.837
<i>The Autobiography of Jack
Hunter.</i> it really moved me.

55
00:02:56.176 --> 00:03:00.170
It's a much more vulnerable.
mature piece of writing.

56
00:03:00.380 --> 00:03:01.380
Thanks.

57
00:03:01.782 --> 00:03:04.809
I mean. I... I
wrote it in prison

58
00:03:04.885 --> 00:03:07.047
partly just to. uh. keep
myself from going insane.

59
00:03:07.120 --> 00:03:09.521
So just to get it published
at all is gratifying. and...

60
00:03:09.589 --> 00:03:12.252
You were in prison for killing
your brother-in-law. right?

61
00:03:13.427 --> 00:03:16.261
Uh. my. uh. ex-wife's
brother-in-law. yeah.

62
00:03:16.863 --> 00:03:18.541
But there's plenty of
stuff out there about that.

63
00:03:18.565 --> 00:03:21.326
- I really don't want to make this about...
- No. no. no. It's just...

64
00:03:21.768 --> 00:03:24.704
ten years ago you were a public
school teacher living in Brooklyn.

65
00:03:25.338 --> 00:03:29.275
and then one summer. you wrote a
novel that was an overnight sensation.

66
00:03:29.342 --> 00:03:32.835
You left your wife and family.
you married your mistress.

67
00:03:32.913 --> 00:03:34.779
you became
suddenly famous and...

68
00:03:35.549 --> 00:03:38.229
I don't know. let's say you drank
a little bit of your own Kool-Aid.

69
00:03:39.186 --> 00:03:40.848
You became
increasingly arrogant.

70
00:03:40.921 --> 00:03:44.414
self-absorbed. reckless.
until one fateful night

71
00:03:44.491 --> 00:03:46.119
on the dark roads of Montauk.

72
00:03:46.193 --> 00:03:47.937
you hit someone and fled
the scene of the crime...

73
00:03:47.961 --> 00:03:50.726
- I'm going somewhere with this.
- I hope so.

74
00:03:50.931 --> 00:03:53.901
You had an enormous
fall from grace.

75
00:03:54.367 --> 00:03:58.828
You went to prison. you served
time. you... lost everything.

76
00:03:59.940 --> 00:04:01.067
And now you're out.

77
00:04:01.141 --> 00:04:03.633
you've gone back to
teaching underprivileged kids.

78
00:04:03.710 --> 00:04:05.679
you have moved to
be closer to your family.

79
00:04:05.746 --> 00:04:07.681
You seem to be
living a quiet life now.

80
00:04:09.382 --> 00:04:10.714
You've come full circle.

81
00:04:12.786 --> 00:04:17.520
So would you say that the redemption
of Noah Solloway is complete?

82
00:04:23.497 --> 00:04:24.497
Um...

83
00:04:28.735 --> 00:04:30.897
Uh. you read the
book. you tell me.

84
00:04:32.839 --> 00:04:34.831
That seems like a
perfect place to stop.

85
00:04:37.310 --> 00:04:39.040
I'm really excited
about this piece.

86
00:04:39.379 --> 00:04:42.713
- People love a comeback story.
- When will they run it. do you know?

87
00:04:43.150 --> 00:04:46.484
Well. it's not up to me. but.
um. they're hoping to time it

88
00:04:46.553 --> 00:04:47.730
with the release of your movie.

89
00:04:47.754 --> 00:04:49.565
Your book is coming out
around then. too. isn't it?

90
00:04:49.589 --> 00:04:50.589
That's right.

91
00:04:51.224 --> 00:04:52.783
It's quite a year you're having.

92
00:04:52.926 --> 00:04:55.452
Oh. um. one more thing.
Are you seeing anyone?

93
00:04:57.531 --> 00:04:59.295
Our readers will want to know.

94
00:05:01.368 --> 00:05:04.998
Uh... no. No. not at the moment.

95
00:05:05.238 --> 00:05:07.230
Really? That surprises me.

96
00:05:08.542 --> 00:05:10.408
Yeah. well. I guess that's. uh.

97
00:05:10.477 --> 00:05:13.311
that's one piece of the puzzle
I haven't quite figured out yet.

98
00:05:14.581 --> 00:05:15.581
There's still time.

99
00:05:16.850 --> 00:05:19.217
Oh. I should
probably turn this off.

100
00:05:19.853 --> 00:05:20.930
You still use those things?

101
00:05:20.954 --> 00:05:23.651
I thought young reporters
these days just used their iPhone.

102
00:05:23.957 --> 00:05:24.981
Well. I'm not that young.

103
00:05:25.058 --> 00:05:27.425
and the batteries on
these things last longer.

104
00:05:27.928 --> 00:05:28.759
The last time I saw one.

105
00:05:28.829 --> 00:05:31.856
I was interviewing a
friend in Freshman Psych.

106
00:05:32.465 --> 00:05:35.799
Oh. you know. speaking of
friends. could I call some of them?

107
00:05:35.869 --> 00:05:39.738
You know. to round out the picture?
Who is Noah Solloway. the man?

108
00:05:40.106 --> 00:05:42.007
Uh. sure. Of course.

109
00:05:42.275 --> 00:05:43.275
I can do that.

110
00:05:43.777 --> 00:05:47.475
I can... talk...
for the article.

111
00:05:47.547 --> 00:05:50.949
You're Petra Ranes. I love your
work. I-I read everything you write.

112
00:05:51.017 --> 00:05:52.713
Oh. thanks. Uh. who are you?

113
00:05:52.786 --> 00:05:54.880
I'm the principal. actually.

114
00:05:55.222 --> 00:05:58.386
Of this. uh. school.

115
00:05:58.458 --> 00:05:59.926
But we're also friends.

116
00:05:59.993 --> 00:06:03.486
And I'm a novelist. too. so we have
that whole simpatico thing going. and...

117
00:06:03.563 --> 00:06:05.575
You know what? I'll. uh. I'll
think of a couple of names

118
00:06:05.599 --> 00:06:07.227
- and get back to you.
- Great.

119
00:06:07.367 --> 00:06:08.995
- Thank you for your time.
- Thank you.

120
00:06:17.644 --> 00:06:19.442
<i>Vanity Fair?</i>

121
00:06:19.713 --> 00:06:21.238
Wow.

122
00:06:21.581 --> 00:06:23.777
This is gonna be big for you.

123
00:06:24.751 --> 00:06:26.617
- We'll see.
- I mean. this is...

124
00:06:27.220 --> 00:06:30.918
top-tier literary recognition.
That's rarified air.

125
00:06:31.224 --> 00:06:32.988
You want to go out?
Celebrate tonight?

126
00:06:33.526 --> 00:06:35.085
Talk about our craft?

127
00:06:35.161 --> 00:06:36.561
Uh. no. I got to. um...

128
00:06:36.630 --> 00:06:37.940
I got to have dinner
with my daughter.

129
00:06:37.964 --> 00:06:40.331
and then I'm gonna be
on set till-till late. so...

130
00:06:40.634 --> 00:06:43.900
"I'm gonna be on set."
Jesus. man. Who are you?

131
00:06:43.970 --> 00:06:46.337
It's okay. I stay
up late. I'll call you.

132
00:06:46.606 --> 00:06:49.371
I mean. I got to buy a beer
for the man who has it all.

133
00:06:49.476 --> 00:06:50.476
Maybe.

134
00:07:02.923 --> 00:07:06.587
- Is Colin coming. or should we just order?
- Uh. no. He'll be here. He just...

135
00:07:07.227 --> 00:07:10.493
When he works. he can get
carried away. lose track of time.

136
00:07:11.364 --> 00:07:12.992
I can't believe you're
getting married.

137
00:07:13.233 --> 00:07:14.826
I know. Me either.

138
00:07:16.703 --> 00:07:18.865
- You okay?
- Yeah. I'm fine.

139
00:07:20.473 --> 00:07:22.271
- How's work?
- Work's fine.

140
00:07:25.845 --> 00:07:26.845
Whit.

141
00:07:28.548 --> 00:07:29.572
Is something wrong?

142
00:07:30.016 --> 00:07:32.508
I don't want to pry.
but you seem kind of.

143
00:07:32.585 --> 00:07:34.247
- I don't know.
- I'm just tired. Dad.

144
00:07:34.321 --> 00:07:37.120
I have to be at the gallery
by 7:00 every morning.

145
00:07:37.190 --> 00:07:39.335
We don't have air conditioning
'cause Andrea's too cheap.

146
00:07:39.359 --> 00:07:41.760
It's hot as hell and. you
know. I'm doing everything:

147
00:07:41.828 --> 00:07:44.457
I hang the art. I man the
phones. I keep the books.

148
00:07:44.631 --> 00:07:47.533
All she does is check her
Raya profile and freak out.

149
00:07:47.600 --> 00:07:48.600
What's a...

150
00:07:48.735 --> 00:07:50.465
Never mind. So you
don't like this job?

151
00:07:50.537 --> 00:07:52.665
I mean. it beats copy
editing <i>Art Forum.</i>

152
00:07:53.239 --> 00:07:55.037
Well. maybe you could
find another gallery

153
00:07:55.108 --> 00:07:56.485
where the boss is a
little more reasonable.

154
00:07:56.509 --> 00:07:57.875
I can't quit. We need the money.

155
00:07:57.944 --> 00:08:00.539
Colin still can't work 'cause
of his visa situation. so...

156
00:08:01.681 --> 00:08:04.674
Well. would it help if I gave
you the money. just to...

157
00:08:04.751 --> 00:08:07.516
Oh. no. Thanks. Dad.
That's not it. It's just that...

158
00:08:07.721 --> 00:08:10.566
Like. when I come home from a long
day of work and I just want to. you know.

159
00:08:10.590 --> 00:08:12.430
have a glass of wine and
watch <i>The Kardashians.</i>

160
00:08:12.459 --> 00:08:14.655
I can't because Colin's
all over me to study.

161
00:08:14.928 --> 00:08:17.090
- Study?
- Yeah. for his immigration interview.

162
00:08:17.163 --> 00:08:18.741
You know. they put
us in separate rooms.

163
00:08:18.765 --> 00:08:20.996
and if we don't get every
single question perfectly.

164
00:08:21.067 --> 00:08:24.504
Colin doesn't get his citizenship.
Oh. hold on. hold on. Thank you.

165
00:08:28.308 --> 00:08:29.401
What?

166
00:08:29.943 --> 00:08:31.275
You remind me of your mother.

167
00:08:31.745 --> 00:08:34.544
- Because I'm an alcoholic?
- No.

168
00:08:35.815 --> 00:08:37.283
'Cause you're so beautiful.

169
00:08:39.786 --> 00:08:40.786
Thanks.

170
00:08:42.355 --> 00:08:43.355
Whitney...

171
00:08:45.592 --> 00:08:48.118
this marriage thing. you
don't have to do it. you know.

172
00:08:48.895 --> 00:08:49.895
It seems rushed.

173
00:08:49.963 --> 00:08:51.295
Yeah. but actually. Dad. I do.

174
00:08:51.364 --> 00:08:53.765
because if I don't. then
Colin has to leave the country.

175
00:08:53.833 --> 00:08:55.324
Well. not forever. right?

176
00:08:55.402 --> 00:08:56.762
I mean. maybe
that's for the best.

177
00:08:56.803 --> 00:08:58.738
He can go home. he can
establish himself there.

178
00:08:58.805 --> 00:09:00.933
and then apply for
citizenship on his own merit.

179
00:09:01.007 --> 00:09:03.019
What are you talking about?
I'm not gonna let him get deported.

180
00:09:03.043 --> 00:09:04.043
I-I love him.

181
00:09:04.244 --> 00:09:05.244
I just...

182
00:09:06.513 --> 00:09:08.914
I don't think it's supposed
to be this hard. Whitney.

183
00:09:09.582 --> 00:09:11.244
You are so young.

184
00:09:11.551 --> 00:09:12.985
It's too early to be this hard.

185
00:09:13.053 --> 00:09:15.079
I don't know if you
remember. Mr. Big Shot.

186
00:09:15.155 --> 00:09:16.835
but you were a
struggling artist once. too.

187
00:09:16.890 --> 00:09:18.358
Mom didn't leave you.

188
00:09:18.725 --> 00:09:20.990
I mean. you left her
20 years later. but...

189
00:09:24.731 --> 00:09:26.597
Whitney. I... I had a job.

190
00:09:27.901 --> 00:09:29.096
I was a teacher.

191
00:09:29.369 --> 00:09:31.201
I never let your
mother support me.

192
00:09:31.471 --> 00:09:32.882
Look. I'm not saying
he's not a good guy...

193
00:09:32.906 --> 00:09:34.568
Sorry. Sorry. Mr. Solloway.

194
00:09:34.641 --> 00:09:35.641
Hi.

195
00:09:36.109 --> 00:09:38.874
- Whit. How you doing?
- Hi.

196
00:09:39.045 --> 00:09:41.776
I got a bit lost in the work.

197
00:09:41.848 --> 00:09:42.848
Have we ordered?

198
00:09:44.651 --> 00:09:45.651
No. Here.

199
00:09:46.352 --> 00:09:47.752
- Here you go.
- Oh. thanks.

200
00:09:51.925 --> 00:09:53.188
Do they do vegan?

201
00:10:05.438 --> 00:10:07.498
- Hi.
<i>- Hi.</i>

202
00:10:08.875 --> 00:10:10.207
Long time.

203
00:10:11.444 --> 00:10:14.676
<i>Um... I know. At
least a month. right?</i>

204
00:10:16.249 --> 00:10:17.581
It's three. actually.

205
00:10:18.685 --> 00:10:22.645
<i>Has it been three months? Wow.
Time really does fly when you're busy.</i>

206
00:10:25.658 --> 00:10:26.921
Why are you calling. Janelle?

207
00:10:26.993 --> 00:10:30.521
<i>I feel badly about the way
things ended between us.</i>

208
00:10:30.897 --> 00:10:34.197
You mean. when you disappeared
after my ex-wife's boyfriend's funeral

209
00:10:34.267 --> 00:10:35.667
and then never
returned my calls?

210
00:10:35.735 --> 00:10:38.364
<i>Yes. I'd actually like to
explain some things in person.</i>

211
00:10:38.438 --> 00:10:41.738
<i>- Are you free tonight?</i>
- Uh... it'd have to be pretty late.

212
00:10:42.709 --> 00:10:43.904
<i>I don't mind waiting up.</i>

213
00:10:51.651 --> 00:10:55.088
What am I gonna do? I
can't stop thinking about you.

214
00:10:55.555 --> 00:10:56.614
I like you.

215
00:10:57.023 --> 00:10:58.719
I like everything about you.

216
00:10:59.459 --> 00:11:01.099
I could be wanted
in four states.

217
00:11:01.761 --> 00:11:03.753
- Helen.
- Shh!

218
00:11:03.830 --> 00:11:05.321
I'll take my chances.

219
00:11:05.899 --> 00:11:07.868
We don't know anything
about each other.

220
00:11:10.770 --> 00:11:13.069
I am never gonna leave my wife.

221
00:11:14.440 --> 00:11:18.343
- I don't expect you to.
- And she can never find out.

222
00:11:19.078 --> 00:11:20.307
I understand.

223
00:11:20.446 --> 00:11:23.610
- You still want to do this?
- Yes.

224
00:11:28.454 --> 00:11:29.786
And cut.

225
00:11:29.856 --> 00:11:31.722
- All right.
- Wasn't that great?

226
00:11:31.791 --> 00:11:33.817
They're so great together.

227
00:11:33.893 --> 00:11:35.191
Why are you here?

228
00:11:35.495 --> 00:11:36.839
- You come... You looking for me?
- Oh...

229
00:11:36.863 --> 00:11:39.332
Oh. no. Uh. I might have a...

230
00:11:40.099 --> 00:11:43.069
- sort of a work opportunity here.
- What? On the movie?

231
00:11:43.403 --> 00:11:46.567
No. no. no. no. no. just through
people connected with the movie.

232
00:11:46.639 --> 00:11:49.159
I don't want to say too much
about it in case it doesn't happen.

233
00:11:50.643 --> 00:11:52.635
How was dinner with.
uh. Colin and Whitney?

234
00:11:53.446 --> 00:11:54.446
It was fine.

235
00:11:56.516 --> 00:11:58.160
